"113 Before a treatment regimen can be decided, then, bacteriological confirmation of the germ's identity is necessary. # Organization of Care\nUsing the short-term treatment makes handling a large number of cases possible; but hospitalization is usually necessary. 113 \n\n# Chemoprophylaxis for the Patient's Household\nChemoprophylaxis for people who are in direct contact with a patient is not recommended. 114 If it is administered, however, rifampin should be used in a dose of 600 mg for adults and 10 mg/kg for children, twice a day for two days."